         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">August 12 [186]2 ¶ editorial addition. ¶ Sir. ¶  ¶ I am directed by the Council of the Acclimatisation Society to request that you will be good enough to bring before the Trustees of the Royal Park th...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">62.08.12<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From George Sprigg</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 62/573, unit 1, p. 377, VPRS 2225 outward letter press copy books, Acclimatisation Society of Victoria, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>August 12 [186]2<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am directed by the Council of the Acclimatisation Society to request that you will be good enough to bring before the Trustees of the Royal Park the necessity of at once applying to the Honble the Commissioner of Lands &amp; Survey for the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Deed</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of conveyance for the Park, as mentioned in the Gazette of April 23rd 1862.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>'Lands to be permanently Reserved, etc',<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Victoria<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">government gazette</seg>,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>23 April 1862, p. 687, first published in the issue of 25 March, p. 529.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M, as secretary to the Royal Park trustees,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>requested the Crown Grant on 16 August (letter not found), to which C. Hodgkinson to M, 30 August 1862 is a reply setting out necessary preliminary steps.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Theodotus John Sumner, William Lyall, John Pinney Bear, Thomas Black, and three Government officers William Wilkinson Wardell, Inspector-General of Public Works, Ferdinand Mueller, Government Botanist and Clement Hodgkinson,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Assistant Commissioner of Lands and Survey,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>were appointed Trustees of the site on10 March 1862, and announced in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Victoria government gazette</seg>,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>25 March<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1862, p.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>529.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your most Obedt Servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Geo Sprigg</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Secretary</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">To Ferdinand Mueller Esq MD. Ph.D. FR.S.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Government Botanist</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Director of the Botanic Gardens</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">&amp;c. <space unit="chars" quantity="2"/>&amp;c. <space unit="chars" quantity="2"/>&amp;c.</p>
         </div>
